    "SUMMARY": "The Stade Francis-Le Blé is a multi-use stadium in Brest, France.  It is currently used mostly for football matches and is the home stadium of Stade Brestois 29. The stadium is able to hold 15,220 spectators. The stadium is named for Francis Le Blé, former mayor of Brest who died in 1982.\n\n"
